reviews.review: I’ll admit there was a lot to take in but it didn’t ruin anything for me. I still enjoyed it.

It's a whole lot of ok. It's a fun, messy movie that manages to thrill but should have slowed down and had more focus. The Rey and Kylo stuff is all great. Ian MacDermid is incredible. Some of the Leia stuff is wonky but considering the tragic situation this production was put in I'll totally give them a pass on that. Some of the worst parts of the story feel like bad fan fiction, and unlike The Last Jedi this movie isn't taking bold chances and diving into new territory. This movie is, for better or worse, all about tying things up with a bow. But it's full of action, comedy, heartfelt moments, and some great new characters. Unfortunately it's also full of sloppy, convenient writing. It isn't the best Star Wars movie by any means, but it's still a satisfying enough conclusion to their story.

Just a re-tread of previous films and themes. Nothing new to say at all. I would have much rather they embraced the risky changes of the last film and given us something more meaningful then simple nostalgia feeding
Jammed packed with action from star to finish. Enjoyable fun theater experience. Fitting end to one of the most infamous story's of all time.

Its too late to be saved , this trilogy is going down in history as a waste , nothing about all 3 films feels like starwars other than them bring back original characters, still no jedi lightsaber fights just 2 kids playing with laser swords , story is ok but thia should of been the 2 film in my opinion its like the last jedi didnt even exist
An abomination. I'm utterly shocked that JJ Abrams made something this bad.
This movie turns the whole trilogy into a bigger mess than it already was. Dumb ideas, too many characters and an over the top ending made me leave the theater with a bitter aftertaste.
Ignore what the critics say and watch this movie. Pretty solid overall.
The critics couldn't be more wrong. It's like we watched entirely different movies.
Great final film in the series and a fitting end to the saga
